<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9727502544484></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9727502544484><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=9727502544484>RE: Beginning Cleric</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=803><span id=Scholar>GiddyGonzalus</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>155 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Oct 28th 12:24 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.29]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First of all, max out your Wisdom with your starting points. I personally favour putting any reamaining points into Strength (but then I like playing Halfling Clerics &lt;now&gt; and they are a little weaker than Dwarves). Your strength should be around 80 to 85 min just so you can wear decent armour and still carry a bit of loot.<br><br>There are plenty of good hunting spots for beginners on Faydwer. Butcher is good and the Chessboard there will be great when you get a little higher. Greater Faydark is also good and hunting those orcs really helps with your faction. BTW keep any bone chips you find. You can turn these into either the Paladin Guild in Kaladim or the Cleric Guild in Felwithe. It's good xp and good faction.<br><br>Just so you know, playing a Dwarven Cleric can get a little rough. In groups, Clerics are often relegated to Healer only (a VERY important role, but can be a little boring for some). Also, Dwarves get a xp penalty (not sure what it is for Dwarven Clerics), whereas Halflings actually get an xp bonus (it's +15% for Halfling Warriors, I think it's about +10% for Halfling Clerics). Just keep this in mind if you're interested in leveling quick.<br><br>Naturally, Clerics are one of the most sought after classes when grouping. I've been in many groups with 4 or 5 members and we are doing perfectly fine. Then a Cleric zones in and advertises they're looking for a group and we grab them, not because we need him (though they are VERY handy) but because we don't want one of the other groups to get an edge on us :P<br>&nbsp;<br>________<br><br>I've travelled this world and have seen many wondrous things. You are not one of them.</td></tr>
